-- India May Grant Voting Rights to Overseas Residents, Press Trust Reports
-- Thomas Abraham
-- 2010-06-13T05:53:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/india-may-grant-voting-rights-to-overseas-residents-press-trust-reports.html

          
          
              India may grant voting rights to
citizens living overseas after a ministerial panel cleared a
draft bill on the matter, the Press Trust of India reported,
citing Overseas Indian Affairs Minister Vayalar Ravi. The bill
will now be placed before the cabinet for approval, the minister
told the news agency.  
